---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What roles are you considering?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Head of Design, VP Design, Chief Design Officer, Chief Experience Officer — the executive leadership tier. Not considering pure individual-contributor roles, design-management roles below Director, or contract work outside Precocity's existing book."}
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where will you work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Dallas, hybrid with travel, or fully remote. Relocation is on the table for the right leadership role — international included. Will not relocate for a fast-growth startup whose runway is the recruiter's main selling point."}
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What companies are interesting?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Companies where design has earned a real seat and the CEO can name three things their best designer shipped last quarter. Specifically interested in flagship consumer and tooling companies — LEGO, Netflix, Apple, Airbnb, and equivalents. Also very interested in traditionally non-tech sectors like John Deere, Caterpillar, Maersk."}
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Will you do a take-home?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No. The work on this site is the take-home. Will do a paid, time-boxed advisory engagement at any stage of the process if it helps both sides decide."}
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are you doing speaking, writing, or advising on the side?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Speaking, occasionally and selectively. Writing, only here. Advisory, only by introduction. Not signing on as a podcast guest unless you've read the work."}
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base title="Contact — uxward" description="Contact Brandon E. B. Ward — executive design leader open to Head of Design, VP Design, CDO, and CXO roles." schema={schema}>
  <style>
    /* contact — Archivo / Swiss system. Quieter caps labels; red bleed kept. */
    .top { padding-top: var(--space-8); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); }
    .top a.back { font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); text-decoration: none; }
    .top a.back:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .name-eyebrow, .section-eyebrow { font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-7); }

    .name-block { padding-top: var(--space-7); padding-bottom: var(--space-9); }
    h1.name { font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 88px); line-height: 0.98; letter-spacing: -0.035em; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; max-width: 18ch; }
    h1.name em { font-style: normal; }
    .deck { font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(19px, 2.2vw, 22px); line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); margin: var(--space-7) 0 0; max-width: 64ch; }

    /* Red bleed CTA */
    .bleed { background: var(--signature); color: var(--offwhite); padding: 120px 0 112px; margin-top: var(--space-9); }
    .bleed .eyebrow { font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(231,231,231,0.82); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
    .bleed h2 { font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 80px); line-height: 0.95; letter-spacing: -0.035em; color: var(--offwhite); margin: 0; max-width: 18ch; }
    .bleed h2 em { font-style: normal; }
    .bleed a.email { margin-top: var(--space-9); display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.45em; font-weight: 800; font-size: clamp(26px, 3.4vw, 40px); line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--offwhite); }
    .bleed a.email .email-text { text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-thickness: 2px; text-underline-offset: 6px; }
    .bleed a.email .send-ico { width: 0.82em; height: 0.82em; }
    .bleed a.email:hover { color: rgba(231,231,231,0.78); }
    .bleed a.email:hover .send-icon,
    .bleed a.email:focus-visible .send-icon { animation: send-fly 0.5s ease; }
    .bleed .kicker { font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(231,231,231,0.82); margin-top: var(--space-5); }

    .section { padding: var(--space-10) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .section-head { font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(28px, 3.4vw, 40px); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 var(--space-8) 0; max-width: 22ch; }
    .section-head em { font-style: normal; }

    .channels, .elsewhere-list, .faq { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .channel-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 200px; gap: var(--space-7); padding: var(--space-5) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: baseline; }
    .channel-row .where { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); }
    .channel-row .what { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--body); }
    .channel-row a.go { font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; text-align: right; }
    .channel-row a.go:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .elsewhere-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr max-content; gap: var(--space-7); padding: var(--space-5) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: baseline; }
    .elsewhere-row .where { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); }
    .elsewhere-row .what { font-size: 17.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); }
    .elsewhere-row a.go { font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; text-align: right; white-space: nowrap; }
    .elsewhere-row a.go:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .faq-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr; gap: var(--space-8); padding: var(--space-7) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: baseline; }
    .faq-row .q { font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.3; color: var(--ink); }
    .faq-row .a { font-size: 17.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--body); max-width: 580px; }
    .faq-row .a em { font-style: italic; }

    .note p { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--body); max-width: 580px; margin: 0; }
    .note .stamp { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); margin-top: var(--space-6); }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .channel-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .channel-row a.go { text-align: left; }
      .elsewhere-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .elsewhere-row a.go { text-align: left; }
      .faq-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container top">
    <div><a class="back" href="/">Back home</a></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container name-block">
    <div class="name-eyebrow">Contact</div>
    <h1 class="name">The <em>direct line</em>, and a few notes on using it.</h1>
    <p class="deck">
      Most of what's here applies to recruiters, hiring managers, and reporters. If you're
      a friend of the work and want to write — even briefer than a cold email is fine.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="bleed">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">Open to</div>
      <h2>The right senior design leadership role. <em>Direct line below.</em></h2>
      <a class="email" href="mailto:brandon@uxward.com">
        <svg class="send-ico" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><g class="send-icon"><path d="M10 14l11 -11" /><path d="M21 3l-6.5 18a.55 .55 0 0 1 -1 0l-3.5 -7l-7 -3.5a.55 .55 0 0 1 0 -1l18 -6.5" /></g></svg>
        <span class="email-text">brandon@uxward.com</span>
      </a>
      <div class="kicker">Read daily · Reply within two business days</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Other channels</div>
      <h3 class="section-head">Email is the right one. <em>The rest are listed for completeness.</em></h3>
      <div class="elsewhere-list">
        <div class="elsewhere-row">
          <span class="where">LinkedIn</span>
          <span class="what">Same record, longer form. Connection requests welcome.</span>
          <a class="go" href="https://linkedin.com/in/brandonebward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/in/brandonebward</a>
        </div>
        <div class="elsewhere-row">
          <span class="where">GitHub</span>
          <span class="what">This site. Everything else is private.</span>
          <a class="go" href="https://github.com/uxward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/uxward</a>
        </div>
        <div class="elsewhere-row">
          <span class="where">Calendar</span>
          <span class="what">By introduction only. Email first, scheduling link after.</span>
          <a class="go" href="mailto:brandon@uxward.com">brandon@uxward.com</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Before you write</div>
      <h3 class="section-head">A few honest answers, <em>so the email is shorter.</em></h3>
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="faq-row">
          <div class="q">What roles are you considering?</div>
          <div class="a">
            Head of Design, VP Design, Chief Design Officer, Chief Experience Officer. <em>The executive leadership tier.</em>
            I am not considering pure individual-contributor roles (unless maybe you're LEGO or a streaming media provider), design-management roles below the
            Director title, or contract work outside Precocity's existing book.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-row">
          <div class="q">Where will you work?</div>
          <div class="a">
            Dallas (where I live), hybrid with travel, or fully remote. Relocation is on the table for the right leadership role — international included. I will not relocate for a fast-growth startup whose
            runway is the recruiter's main selling point.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-row">
          <div class="q">What companies are interesting?</div>
          <div class="a">
            Companies where design has earned a real seat and the CEO can name three things
            their best designer shipped last quarter. I'm specifically interested in flagship
            consumer and tooling companies — LEGO, Netflix, Apple, Airbnb, and the equivalents.
            I'm also very interested in opportunities available in traditionally "non-tech" sectors
            like John Deere, Caterpillar, Maersk, et al.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-row">
          <div class="q">Will you do a take-home?</div>
          <div class="a">
            <em>No.</em> The work on this site is the take-home. I will do a paid, time-boxed
            advisory engagement at any stage of the process if it helps both sides decide.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-row">
          <div class="q">Are you doing speaking, writing, advising on the side?</div>
          <div class="a">
            Speaking, occasionally and selectively. Writing, only here. Advisory, only by
            introduction. I am not signing on as a podcast guest unless you've read the work.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section note">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">A note on response</div>
      <p>
        I read every email that arrives at this address. I reply inside two business days,
        including the ones I'm declining — declining is also a response. If you do not hear
        back inside a week, the email did not arrive; resend.
      </p>
      <div class="stamp">Last revised Q1 2026 · Updated quarterly</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
